lock). I've started work on that, but a couple<br />&gt; of higher interrupts have prevented me from pulling it all together in<br />&gt; time for this merge window...<br /><br />I'm pretty sure we've had at least two trees with the file locking code <br />fixed, but NFS in a status of "unknown".<br /><br />If I recall correctly, the file locking code itself is not that hard: <br />we've done it without the kernel lock in the past (long long ago), and the <br />lock usage doesn't nest (or at least it didn't at some point back then ;). <br />In fact, I think we even do the actual lock data structure allocations <br />outside of the kernel lock exactly because we at one time had a patch that <br />used a spinlock for protection of the lists.<br /><br />(Again, not only my memory, but the code itself may have bitrotted in the <br />meantime, of course).<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
